Durban Two toddler siblings came close to drowning at a South Coast beach on Sunday afternoon.Netcare 911 spokesperson Chris Botha said the two girls aged 3 and 4 had been playing in a tidal pool at Baggies Beach, Warner Beach, when they disappeared under water. Quick action from a bystander and lifeguards saw the children pulled from the water. One was unresponsive, said Botha.By the time paramedics arrived, lifeguards and members of the public had already performed CPR on the 3-year-old. After a few minutes the child started coughing, to the joy of everyone, said Botha.Both children showed near-drowning symptoms on examination, he said. They were taken to hospital. The Mercury